Encrypt Webo IDs in a file
It reads a file which contains Webo ID and write a new file with the same content but with the Encrypted Webo IDs.
The files should be in CSV or JSON format. 'filetype' flag defined which format is used
For CSV file, 'position' flag is mandatory and defined on which position the Webo ID is placed for every lines,
'separator' flag is optional, default is the classic comma
'keep-original-weboid' flag is optional, if it is set, the new Encrypted Webo IDs are placed atthe last position of each line
For JSON file, 'inputjsonkey' flag is mandatory, it defined the key which store the Webo IDs to encrypt
'keep-original-weboid' flag is optional, if it is set, 'outputjsonkey' flag is needed and the new Encrypted Webo IDs is saved using this key
The lines in error will be ignored and an alert message will be displayed on the standard output
